{
  "stem": "9701.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so that conversation went on with him asking me questions and my reluctantly answering him because I did not want to inform him about sex or reproduction.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I sensed his discomfort.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And pretty soon the conversation ended about that topic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went on and talked about other things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of the things that I wanted to mention too about these walks that we did, especially in the spring, summer, and fall, we'd go up in the woods and in one place it was this huge meadow and there were all these wild flowers there.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'd always pick a bouquet of flowers to take home to my mother.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in 1990 when I was back in the village, I took a hike in the woods with my son who accompanied me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I picked a bouquet of flowers, except unfortunately, I had no one to bring them to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But back to 1939, to the children's transport.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were 500 of us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The youngest were twins, six months old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I still remember this young couple handing these children to someone on the train and saying, please take good care of our two babies.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The oldest of us were 17.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was 14 and a half at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I also remember just before I left some feelings that I had and that I shared with my parents, which must've been extremely painful for my parents.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I told them that you probably adopted me and now you no longer want me and you're sending me away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had the vision or the image that I was a gypsy child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Gypsies used to come to our village once or twice a year and pitch their tent.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
